a learned, genetic, or instinctual trait ??
A combination of all three! :) If I had to pick one over the others I'd probably say instinctual.

I would say the literal meaning would be the common deduction and inferences made by superficial or ostensive sensory inputs. It's safe to assume that it mostly depends on how much the individual has interacted with his environment. Therefore, of coarse, common sense is contextual. What may be considered common sense in Japan may be alien information to us, and vise versa.
